<A HREF="FSOUND.html#Functions"><H5>[API function]</A></H5>
<H2><A NAME="FSOUND_SetMixer">FSOUND_SetMixer</A></H2>
Sets a digital mixer type.<BR>
<P>
<B>signed char F_API </B><B> </B><B>FSOUND_SetMixer</B><B>(</B><BR>
<B>int </B><B> </B><I>mixer</I><BR>
<B>);</B><BR>
<H3>Parameters</H3>
<TABLE>
<TR VALIGN=top><TD><I>mixer</I></TD>
<TD>mixer type, see FSOUND_MIXERTYPES for valid parameters and descriptions.<BR>
</TD></TABLE>
<H3>Return Value</H3>
On success, TRUE is returned.<BR>
On failure, (ie if FMOD is already active) FALSE is returned.<BR>
<H3>Remarks</H3>
This function cannot be called after FMOD is already activated with FSOUND_Init.<BR>
It must be called before FSOUND_Init, or after FSOUND_Close.<BR>
This function does not nescessarily need to be called, autodetection will select the <BR>
fastest mixer for your machine.  It is here if you need to test all mixer types for <BR>
debugging purposes, or a mixer has a feature that the autodetected one doesnt.<BR>
(ie low quality mixers or volume ramping)<BR>
___________________<BR>
Supported on the following platforms : Win32, WinCE, Linux, Macintosh, XBox, PlayStation 2, GameCube<BR>
